1
00:00:02,396 --> 00:00:04,687
[Matt] <i>We put Poindexter away
and it changes nothing.</i>

2
00:00:04,688 --> 00:00:07,520
<i>We defend Hector Ayala
and he's still murdered.</i>

3
00:00:07,521 --> 00:00:09,812
<i>Heather's assaulted by Muse
and she thinks Fisk is right.</i>

4
00:00:09,813 --> 00:00:13,229
<i>This, us, what-- what we do,
it feels useless.</i>

5
00:00:13,979 --> 00:00:15,937
[♪ dramatic music playing]

6
00:00:15,938 --> 00:00:17,895
- [gun cocks]
- [Matt] <i>It occurs to me that justice</i>

7
00:00:17,896 --> 00:00:19,228
<i>will not be served today,</i>

8
00:00:19,229 --> 00:00:22,103
<i>because whatever sentence is passed,
Foggy Nelson will still be dead.</i>

9
00:00:22,104 --> 00:00:23,812
[Karen] <i>What're you gonna do
about Daredevil?</i>

10
00:00:23,813 --> 00:00:26,771
[Matt] <i>I'm not him anymore.
And I won't let myself be.</i>

11
00:00:27,396 --> 00:00:28,478
- [gunshot]
- [bullet clattering]

12
00:00:28,479 --> 00:00:29,770
[Matt] <i>A client of mine was shot.</i>

13
00:00:29,771 --> 00:00:32,437
Guess whose logo I found
on the bullet casing?

14
00:00:32,438 --> 00:00:34,812
[Fisk] <i>A task force. Hand-picked by me.</i>

15
00:00:34,813 --> 00:00:36,562
[Gallo] <i>This is every bad apple
in the barrel.</i>

16
00:00:36,563 --> 00:00:38,478
I prefer "motivated individuals."

17
00:00:38,479 --> 00:00:39,603
[Matt] <i>He was celebrating.</i>

18
00:00:39,604 --> 00:00:42,687
Foggy knew the night he died he was
gonna win, and somebody silenced him.

19
00:00:42,688 --> 00:00:45,103
Everyone thought you were just a shooter
on a rampage.

20
00:00:45,104 --> 00:00:46,353
You did it for Fisk.

21
00:00:46,354 --> 00:00:47,770
[Vanessa] <i>I took over the business.</i>

22
00:00:47,771 --> 00:00:50,895
<i>Then he returns
and I really don't know how I feel.</i>

23
00:00:50,896 --> 00:00:53,895
[Matt] But I need you to know,
he sought you out to get to me.

24
00:00:53,896 --> 00:00:56,437
Matt, you're starting to worry me
on a professional level.

25
00:00:56,438 --> 00:00:58,103
[Buck] <i>Ben Poindexter killed
a prison guard</i>

26
00:00:58,104 --> 00:00:59,313
<i>and used his badge to escape.</i>

27
00:01:00,313 --> 00:01:01,770
I know you had Foggy killed.

28
00:01:01,771 --> 00:01:03,270
Your husband, does he know?

29
00:01:03,271 --> 00:01:05,354
[♪ dramatic music playing]

30
00:01:17,479 --> 00:01:20,062
[♪ gospel music playing, Florida Mass
Choir "Storm Cloud Rising"]

31
00:01:20,063 --> 00:01:25,229
<i>- ♪ I see the lightning flashing ♪
- ♪ I see the lightning flashing ♪</i>

32
00:01:26,229 --> 00:01:30,978
<i>- ♪ Heard ♪
- ♪ Heard the thunder roll ♪</i>

33
00:01:30,979 --> 00:01:33,688
- [flies buzzing]
- [gun cocks]

34
00:01:34,396 --> 00:01:36,354
[gunshot]

35
00:01:37,229 --> 00:01:39,896
- [people talking indistinctly]
- [chime over speakers]

36
00:01:52,438 --> 00:01:55,854
The whole FBI corruption scandal,
Agent Nadeem, all that.

37
00:01:56,896 --> 00:01:58,771
It's why my husband was acquitted.

38
00:01:59,813 --> 00:02:01,979
It's only fair it should benefit you, too.

39
00:02:03,646 --> 00:02:06,396
{\an8}[Poindexter] "Release on appeal."

40
00:02:07,438 --> 00:02:09,021
[breathing heavily]

41
00:02:11,229 --> 00:02:12,229
Fisk,

42
00:02:13,354 --> 00:02:14,771
he knows about this?

43
00:02:15,771 --> 00:02:18,604
I haven't seen my husband in a while.

44
00:02:19,938 --> 00:02:23,063
I had you released because I need a favor.

45
00:02:24,979 --> 00:02:26,188
You want me to...

46
00:02:28,688 --> 00:02:29,813
kill someone.

47
00:02:31,729 --> 00:02:34,854
A thief called Benjamin Cafaro

48
00:02:35,896 --> 00:02:38,021
and his lawyer, Foggy Nelson.

49
00:02:40,563 --> 00:02:42,021
I remember him.

50
00:02:43,229 --> 00:02:45,229
Escape the past, do we?

51
00:02:45,979 --> 00:02:48,729
[Vanessa] The case he's involved with
would shine

52
00:02:49,438 --> 00:02:52,479
unwanted light
on some of my business practices.

53
00:02:55,021 --> 00:02:56,771
It has to be soon.

54
00:02:57,896 --> 00:02:59,354
In the next few days.

55
00:03:00,396 --> 00:03:02,688
[woman over PA] <i>Dr. Jane,
seven-five-three-three.</i>

56
00:03:04,021 --> 00:03:06,062
[♪ soft instrumental music playing]

57
00:03:06,063 --> 00:03:07,271
[Vanessa] Benjamin,

58
00:03:08,479 --> 00:03:11,270
I'm offering you a chance
to get your mind back.

59
00:03:11,271 --> 00:03:13,271
Your self...

60
00:03:14,063 --> 00:03:15,521
This is no way to live.

61
00:03:26,563 --> 00:03:30,021
You are the very best
at this type of thing.

62
00:03:30,688 --> 00:03:31,979
That's why I came.

63
00:03:32,896 --> 00:03:35,604
Your history with my husband
isn't part of this.

64
00:03:37,271 --> 00:03:40,562
He's... always part of this.

65
00:03:40,563 --> 00:03:42,896
[♪ tense music playing]

66
00:03:44,979 --> 00:03:46,396
It's a simple offer.

67
00:03:52,396 --> 00:03:54,353
[announcer over PA]
<i>Dr. Patel, six-six-three.</i>

68
00:03:54,354 --> 00:03:55,521
[Vanessa] Trust me.

69
00:03:57,688 --> 00:03:59,688
[♪ tense, unsettling music playing]

70
00:04:04,938 --> 00:04:06,313
[scribbling]

71
00:04:11,354 --> 00:04:13,354
[♪ unsettling music intensifies]

72
00:04:18,896 --> 00:04:20,854
[people shouting indistinctly]

73
00:04:23,813 --> 00:04:24,938
[Vanessa] You're free.

74
00:04:34,313 --> 00:04:36,895
[♪ gospel music playing, The Florida Mass
Choir "Storm Cloud Rising"]

75
00:04:36,896 --> 00:04:38,728
<i>♪ I see the lightning flash ♪</i>

76
00:04:38,729 --> 00:04:39,812
[gun cocks]

77
00:04:39,813 --> 00:04:41,563
<i>♪ See the lightning flash ♪</i>

78
00:04:42,688 --> 00:04:43,687
[muffled conversation]

79
00:04:43,688 --> 00:04:46,938
<i>♪ Heard the thunder roll ♪</i>

80
00:04:48,604 --> 00:04:50,020
<i>♪ Storm cloud... ♪</i>

81
00:04:50,021 --> 00:04:51,603
- [gunshot]
- [Heather] Matt!

82
00:04:51,604 --> 00:04:54,145
- [people screaming]
- [Heather gasping]

83
00:04:54,146 --> 00:04:56,229
[♪ theme music playing]

84
00:05:26,688 --> 00:05:28,688
[♪ theme music continues playing]

85
00:06:33,646 --> 00:06:35,603
[monitor beeping]

86
00:06:35,604 --> 00:06:38,062
[indistinct announcement playing over PA]

87
00:06:38,063 --> 00:06:39,854
[people talking indistinctly]

88
00:06:44,229 --> 00:06:45,438
[coughs softly]

89
00:06:47,604 --> 00:06:48,604
[flinches]

90
00:06:49,396 --> 00:06:50,396
Karen?

91
00:06:54,771 --> 00:06:55,854
It's the drugs.

92
00:06:59,896 --> 00:07:00,938
Heather.

93
00:07:01,646 --> 00:07:03,978
You okay? [gulps]

94
00:07:03,979 --> 00:07:06,020
- Fine.
- [Matt exhales]

95
00:07:06,021 --> 00:07:07,353
I...

96
00:07:07,354 --> 00:07:09,562
[swallows, exhales]

97
00:07:09,563 --> 00:07:10,688
Water?

98
00:07:11,521 --> 00:07:13,063
[exhales, sips]

99
00:07:14,063 --> 00:07:15,104
Fisk?

100
00:07:16,438 --> 00:07:17,521
You saved his life.

101
00:07:18,229 --> 00:07:19,271
Yeah.

102
00:07:19,979 --> 00:07:24,188
I heard someone scream "gun"
and I just reacted. Poindexter?

103
00:07:24,813 --> 00:07:26,313
[Kirsten] He's still at large.

104
00:07:28,063 --> 00:07:31,229
Kirsten, Vanessa Fisk
ordered the hit on Foggy.

105
00:07:32,854 --> 00:07:36,270
Listen, the case Foggy was working on,
can you get me access to it from--

106
00:07:36,271 --> 00:07:38,020
Hey, listen,
you're on a ton of medication.

107
00:07:38,021 --> 00:07:39,478
[Matt] I know how this sounds.

108
00:07:39,479 --> 00:07:42,020
I really don't think you do.
I don't think you do. Okay?

109
00:07:42,021 --> 00:07:44,228
- [liquid pouring]
- [Vanessa shudders]

110
00:07:44,229 --> 00:07:45,563
[Vanessa] I'm still shaking.

111
00:07:47,813 --> 00:07:50,938
- All I care is that you're still alive.
- [Vanessa sighs]

112
00:07:53,771 --> 00:07:55,771
[♪ suspenseful music playing]

113
00:07:58,438 --> 00:07:59,896
[coughs]

114
00:08:00,438 --> 00:08:01,604
[exhales deeply]

115
00:08:07,188 --> 00:08:08,396
Vanessa...

116
00:08:09,563 --> 00:08:10,604
I know.

117
00:08:13,271 --> 00:08:14,354
I know.

118
00:08:15,688 --> 00:08:16,896
[sighs]

119
00:08:21,396 --> 00:08:24,021
[♪ tense music playing]

120
00:08:24,854 --> 00:08:25,896
[Vanessa sighs]

121
00:08:29,604 --> 00:08:31,478
[Matt] <i>Foggy knew
he was gonna win his case.</i>

122
00:08:31,479 --> 00:08:34,562
I talked to Josie. He'd already
opened a bottle of O'Melveny's.

123
00:08:34,563 --> 00:08:36,270
I remember him drinking it.

124
00:08:36,271 --> 00:08:37,895
- [Matt] Right?
- He was saying that he was

125
00:08:37,896 --> 00:08:40,853
celebrating an early win,
but I think it was just bluster.

126
00:08:40,854 --> 00:08:42,687
No, it wasn't.
I think he was sitting on something

127
00:08:42,688 --> 00:08:44,103
the Fisks didn't want exposed.

128
00:08:44,104 --> 00:08:46,312
You do realize
they were the ones getting shot at.

129
00:08:46,313 --> 00:08:48,562
- I know. Hey. I know it was them.
- [Kirsten] Yeah.

130
00:08:48,563 --> 00:08:50,187
I just don't know why.

131
00:08:50,188 --> 00:08:52,520
Do you remember anything else
from that night?

132
00:08:52,521 --> 00:08:55,478
[sighs] Um...

133
00:08:55,479 --> 00:08:59,312
I remember him saying that he was
gonna be filing a motion to dismiss.

134
00:08:59,313 --> 00:09:00,395
I need to see it.

135
00:09:00,396 --> 00:09:01,937
You can't, because it wasn't filed.

136
00:09:01,938 --> 00:09:03,770
[Matt] Then I need to get out of here
and find it.

137
00:09:03,771 --> 00:09:04,896
[Kirsten] Hey, hey. Just...

138
00:09:06,104 --> 00:09:09,271
[Fisk] <i>You moved millions
through Red Hook.</i>

139
00:09:10,104 --> 00:09:11,771
Now that I'm mayor,

140
00:09:12,604 --> 00:09:15,021
we can move billions.

141
00:09:16,146 --> 00:09:18,603
[♪ tense music playing]

142
00:09:18,604 --> 00:09:23,812
- Gallo and the police.
- Luca. Hmm.

143
00:09:23,813 --> 00:09:26,979
- And the gangs?
- All of it architecture.

144
00:09:29,271 --> 00:09:32,188
I-I ran to save the city.

145
00:09:32,896 --> 00:09:35,479
But opportunities present themselves.

146
00:09:39,521 --> 00:09:41,103
Matt, just-- You gotta take it easy, Matt.

147
00:09:41,104 --> 00:09:42,728
[Matt] I'm not losing it, Heather.

148
00:09:42,729 --> 00:09:46,520
However much you think you know Fisk,
you don't. And it's really dangerous.

149
00:09:46,521 --> 00:09:48,978
I'm sorry you don't believe me,
but I'm telling you the truth.

150
00:09:48,979 --> 00:09:50,688
[breathing heavily]

151
00:09:53,229 --> 00:09:55,396
[Heather] I think it's better I come back
once you've...

152
00:09:57,021 --> 00:09:58,229
had some rest.

153
00:09:59,229 --> 00:10:01,271
[♪ melancholy music playing]

154
00:10:03,979 --> 00:10:05,270
[Kirsten] I'll be out in a second.

155
00:10:05,271 --> 00:10:07,354
[♪ music turns eerie]

156
00:10:11,021 --> 00:10:12,270
[Fisk] <i>They're gonna go out there</i>

157
00:10:12,271 --> 00:10:14,645
<i>and hunt down not only Poindexter,
but all vigilantes!</i>

158
00:10:14,646 --> 00:10:19,228
There'll be no body cams,
no due process, no warrants!

159
00:10:19,229 --> 00:10:22,228
[Gallo] Sir, that not only goes against
the operating principles of the NYPD,

160
00:10:22,229 --> 00:10:24,978
it's illegal. I mean, next, you'll be
condoning the use of lethal force.

161
00:10:24,979 --> 00:10:29,103
"Condoning"? Absolutely not.
Encouraging, Gallo! Encouraging!

162
00:10:29,104 --> 00:10:33,187
I want the bridges shut down!
I want the tunnels closed!

163
00:10:33,188 --> 00:10:38,145
Sir, a lone gunman attacking
the mayor is a massive affront.

164
00:10:38,146 --> 00:10:41,978
Of course, I see that.
But to seal the city,

165
00:10:41,979 --> 00:10:46,812
you need a large scale, real,
and present threat to public safety.

166
00:10:46,813 --> 00:10:50,229
Sheila, your concerns are noted.

167
00:10:52,271 --> 00:10:54,604
Now you all have a job to do.

168
00:10:58,771 --> 00:11:00,313
Buck, one moment, please.

169
00:11:05,979 --> 00:11:08,604
Tell me, what's Matt Murdock's condition?

170
00:11:09,896 --> 00:11:12,646
Stable. Recovering at Metro-General.

171
00:11:13,313 --> 00:11:17,104
Murdock saving you does complicate
the optics of things, somewhat.

172
00:11:18,771 --> 00:11:19,771
No.

173
00:11:21,021 --> 00:11:22,188
Quite the opposite.

174
00:11:23,646 --> 00:11:28,979
Imagine if our fearless lawyer
from Hell's Kitchen...

175
00:11:30,938 --> 00:11:33,853
were to succumb to his wounds.

176
00:11:33,854 --> 00:11:36,438
Wounds he's sustained
by trying to save the mayor.

177
00:11:37,479 --> 00:11:38,937
In this case,

178
00:11:38,938 --> 00:11:42,978
a dead hero
is better than a live vigilante.

179
00:11:42,979 --> 00:11:45,104
[♪ tense music playing]

180
00:11:52,479 --> 00:11:56,562
[Kirsten] Matt, I'm really, really glad
that you're gonna be okay. I am.

181
00:11:56,563 --> 00:11:58,437
But we're gonna have to have a serious
conversation

182
00:11:58,438 --> 00:12:00,021
on the other side of this, all right?

183
00:12:04,521 --> 00:12:06,312
[announcer over PA]
<i>Dr. Calvinson, three-zero-six.</i>

184
00:12:06,313 --> 00:12:09,354
<i>- Dr. Calvinson, three-zero-six.</i>
- [footsteps receding]

185
00:12:12,313 --> 00:12:15,313
[♪ tense, dramatic music playing]

186
00:12:22,854 --> 00:12:27,396
I've been giving thought
to what you said earlier about threats

187
00:12:28,604 --> 00:12:29,813
and public safety.

188
00:12:31,604 --> 00:12:32,771
[Sheila] I'm so glad, sir.

189
00:12:33,521 --> 00:12:37,813
Sometimes our reactions are worse
than the offenses that cause them.

190
00:12:39,854 --> 00:12:41,021
[Fisk] Sheila, I've...

191
00:12:45,354 --> 00:12:50,604
In business, there's always
a tipping point in a negotiation.

192
00:12:51,771 --> 00:12:54,521
We are in that place with this city.

193
00:12:56,771 --> 00:12:58,521
It just needs a little push...

194
00:13:00,479 --> 00:13:03,479
and they'll come to us with open arms.

195
00:13:05,979 --> 00:13:08,771
And what would that push be?

196
00:13:12,563 --> 00:13:14,521
You're a very perceptive woman.

197
00:13:16,938 --> 00:13:22,188
I imagine that you know
who in my staff is loyal and who is not.

198
00:13:24,521 --> 00:13:25,771
People talk to you.

199
00:13:28,563 --> 00:13:32,563
Yeah, yeah, you can say that
I've got an ear to the ground here.

200
00:13:33,813 --> 00:13:34,813
Good.

201
00:13:36,396 --> 00:13:39,979
Send everyone
who's not completely on board...

202
00:13:41,438 --> 00:13:42,479
home.

203
00:13:43,146 --> 00:13:44,563
[chuckles softly]

204
00:13:49,479 --> 00:13:50,479
Yes, sir.

205
00:13:51,188 --> 00:13:53,188
[♪ tense music playing]

206
00:13:54,021 --> 00:13:57,354
On your way out, can you send in
our friend from Con Ed?

207
00:14:02,271 --> 00:14:04,271
[♪ woman vocalizing]

208
00:14:14,563 --> 00:14:15,562
[elevator dings]

209
00:14:15,563 --> 00:14:17,688
{\an8}[people talking indistinctly]

210
00:14:20,063 --> 00:14:23,645
{\an8}[announcer over PA] <i>Outpatient
department manager, please dial 5-7-3.</i>

211
00:14:23,646 --> 00:14:25,688
<i>Outpatient department manager.</i>

212
00:14:27,563 --> 00:14:29,146
[footsteps approaching]

213
00:14:33,354 --> 00:14:34,604
[Gallo] We need to talk.

214
00:14:37,938 --> 00:14:38,938
Okay.

215
00:14:40,313 --> 00:14:42,229
[Gallo] I mean, you see
what's happening, right?

216
00:14:43,063 --> 00:14:44,479
I know you do.

217
00:14:45,396 --> 00:14:47,020
- First, he guts the force.
- [door opens]

218
00:14:47,021 --> 00:14:49,937
- [people talking indistinctly]
- Crime spikes,

219
00:14:49,938 --> 00:14:51,729
probably due to friends of his.

220
00:14:52,313 --> 00:14:53,645
And then... [chuckles]

221
00:14:53,646 --> 00:14:57,395
...he turns a bunch of rogue cops
into his own personal militia,

222
00:14:57,396 --> 00:14:59,770
sends them out as a kill squad
against the vigilantes,

223
00:14:59,771 --> 00:15:02,728
and now he's trying to get his hands
on the power switch to the city?

224
00:15:02,729 --> 00:15:05,353
It sounds like
you've got ears in the walls.

225
00:15:05,354 --> 00:15:08,312
There are still sane people
in the building.

226
00:15:08,313 --> 00:15:10,563
And I am betting that you're one of them.

227
00:15:12,729 --> 00:15:14,728
[♪ music playing, The Spinowitz Experience
"Killing Me Softly With his Song"]

228
00:15:14,729 --> 00:15:16,313
[people talking indistinctly]

229
00:15:18,146 --> 00:15:20,146
[footsteps echoing]

230
00:15:24,188 --> 00:15:26,188
[♪ music turns eerie]

231
00:15:30,979 --> 00:15:32,437
[Gallo] <i>I'm going up the ladder.</i>

232
00:15:32,438 --> 00:15:34,562
The Governor, State Supreme Court.

233
00:15:34,563 --> 00:15:36,770
Uh, th-this is still the mayor's office.
Not the Kingpin's.

234
00:15:36,771 --> 00:15:38,603
And he is still subject to the law.

235
00:15:38,604 --> 00:15:43,188
- [sighs]
- And I'm hoping for your support.

236
00:15:44,563 --> 00:15:46,563
[♪ music playing, The Spinowitz Experience
"Killing Me Softly With his Song"]

237
00:15:47,438 --> 00:15:49,188
[♪ music turns tense]

238
00:15:51,021 --> 00:15:54,521
- When?
- Tomorrow. I leave for Albany first thing.

239
00:15:55,229 --> 00:15:57,688
Yeah, well, there's no way
I can go with you.

240
00:15:58,354 --> 00:16:02,145
But if you need me to put in a word,
you got it.

241
00:16:02,146 --> 00:16:04,603
- I appreciate that, Sheila.
- Yeah.

242
00:16:04,604 --> 00:16:05,978
[Gallo] We'll get through this.

243
00:16:05,979 --> 00:16:07,896
- The city always does.
- Hmm.

244
00:16:09,271 --> 00:16:10,937
- [Gallo] You watch your back.
- [sighs]

245
00:16:10,938 --> 00:16:13,353
Always. You too.

246
00:16:13,354 --> 00:16:16,146
[♪ jazz music playing, Roberta Flack,
"Killing Me Softly With his Song"]

247
00:16:18,396 --> 00:16:20,354
[indistinct conversation]

248
00:16:23,646 --> 00:16:25,646
[clock ticking]

249
00:16:30,938 --> 00:16:32,187
[loud clang]

250
00:16:32,188 --> 00:16:34,104
- [alarm blaring]
- [people talking indistinctly]

251
00:16:35,271 --> 00:16:38,313
<i>♪ Strumming my pain with his fingers ♪</i>

252
00:16:39,063 --> 00:16:41,979
<i>♪ Singing my life with his words ♪</i>

253
00:16:43,063 --> 00:16:49,687
<i>♪ Killing me softly with his song ♪</i>

254
00:16:49,688 --> 00:16:53,853
<i>♪ Telling my whole life with his words ♪</i>

255
00:16:53,854 --> 00:16:57,854
<i>♪ Killing me softly... ♪</i>

256
00:16:59,104 --> 00:17:01,229
<i>♪ Oh... ♪</i>

257
00:17:11,813 --> 00:17:13,813
[♪ tense, suspenseful music playing]

258
00:17:14,563 --> 00:17:16,895
[helicopter whirring]

259
00:17:16,896 --> 00:17:18,353
[siren blaring]

260
00:17:18,354 --> 00:17:19,771
[horns honking]

261
00:17:21,688 --> 00:17:23,478
[people talking indistinctly]

262
00:17:23,479 --> 00:17:24,978
[sirens continue blaring]

263
00:17:24,979 --> 00:17:26,854
[helicopter whirring]

264
00:17:28,104 --> 00:17:29,479
[door opens]

265
00:17:30,979 --> 00:17:32,688
[breathes deeply]

266
00:17:35,188 --> 00:17:37,188
[♪ suspenseful music playing]

267
00:17:43,188 --> 00:17:44,353
[groans softly]

268
00:17:44,354 --> 00:17:46,104
[helicopter whirring continues]

269
00:17:47,646 --> 00:17:49,104
[exhales]

270
00:17:52,396 --> 00:17:55,729
You're pretty much the last person
I expected to find here. [sighs]

271
00:17:57,063 --> 00:17:59,146
[Frank] You know
you're a wall-to-wall asshole?

272
00:17:59,771 --> 00:18:04,478
Power goes out, you got nothing to make
a goddamn pot of coffee in this house.

273
00:18:04,479 --> 00:18:06,812
Well, not everyone lives
in a fallout shelter, Frank.

274
00:18:06,813 --> 00:18:09,812
Is that a new costume?
What do they call you now?

275
00:18:09,813 --> 00:18:11,228
"Nightgown man"?

276
00:18:11,229 --> 00:18:14,895
[Matt] What about you?
Aftershave and a haircut. That all for me?

277
00:18:14,896 --> 00:18:16,978
[Frank] Yeah. Yeah, I did it for you.

278
00:18:16,979 --> 00:18:18,812
I thought this wasn't your fight.

279
00:18:18,813 --> 00:18:21,646
[Frank] Yeah, well, I got a phone call
that changed my mind.

280
00:18:22,396 --> 00:18:23,728
Care to be more specific?

281
00:18:23,729 --> 00:18:24,938
No, I do not.

282
00:18:25,771 --> 00:18:28,062
I made a promise
I was gonna get you out of here alive.

283
00:18:28,063 --> 00:18:29,813
That's exactly what I'm gonna do.

284
00:18:30,563 --> 00:18:33,228
Northwest side of the house,
there's a van full of shit bags.

285
00:18:33,229 --> 00:18:35,270
- You clocked that?
- Yep. [groans softly]

286
00:18:35,271 --> 00:18:38,187
I'll tell you right now, they come up
here, I'm not playing patty cake

287
00:18:38,188 --> 00:18:41,354
with these fan boys. I'm choppin' 'em up.
You understand me?

288
00:18:41,979 --> 00:18:43,812
I'm not sure I want
that kind of help, Frank.

289
00:18:43,813 --> 00:18:46,479
- Well, that's the kind of help you've got.
- [Matt groans]

290
00:18:50,646 --> 00:18:51,646
Hey, Red.

291
00:18:52,896 --> 00:18:53,938
Yeah.

292
00:18:54,896 --> 00:18:56,854
Why would you take a bullet
for that asshole?

293
00:18:58,729 --> 00:19:01,978
[Matt exhales] That is a good question.

294
00:19:01,979 --> 00:19:04,270
[♪ unsettling music playing]

295
00:19:04,271 --> 00:19:05,687
[helicopter whirring]

296
00:19:05,688 --> 00:19:07,646
[engine revving]

297
00:19:10,771 --> 00:19:12,438
[tires screeching]

298
00:19:14,479 --> 00:19:16,603
We'll surprise him on inspection.
Now, let's move.

299
00:19:16,604 --> 00:19:18,520
[indistinct police chatter over radio]

300
00:19:18,521 --> 00:19:20,604
[♪ dramatic music playing]

301
00:19:23,771 --> 00:19:24,813
[door clangs open]

302
00:19:26,396 --> 00:19:28,438
[choir vocalizing]

303
00:19:30,729 --> 00:19:32,229
All right. They're on the move.

304
00:19:33,479 --> 00:19:35,229
You're not gonna do it
with your ass hangin' out?

305
00:19:37,438 --> 00:19:39,438
[♪ tense music playing]

306
00:20:10,021 --> 00:20:11,813
[♪ tense music continues]

307
00:20:14,229 --> 00:20:16,437
- [indistinct screaming]
- [officers grunting]

308
00:20:16,438 --> 00:20:19,062
- [rapid gunshots]
- [officers screaming]

309
00:20:19,063 --> 00:20:21,062
[grunting]

310
00:20:21,063 --> 00:20:23,188
[♪ dramatic music playing]

311
00:20:24,271 --> 00:20:27,521
[screaming, grunting]

312
00:20:31,938 --> 00:20:33,979
- [officer] Shit.
- [both grunting]

313
00:20:35,438 --> 00:20:37,063
- [The Punisher grunts]
- [screams]

314
00:20:37,979 --> 00:20:39,271
- [Daredevil] Frank, stop.
- [grunts]

315
00:20:40,896 --> 00:20:42,896
- [gunshots]
- [officer groaning]

316
00:20:44,354 --> 00:20:46,187
[The Punisher grunts]

317
00:20:46,188 --> 00:20:47,978
[groans]

318
00:20:47,979 --> 00:20:49,646
[both grunting]

319
00:20:51,063 --> 00:20:52,563
[both grunting]

320
00:20:54,604 --> 00:20:55,978
[rapid gunfire]

321
00:20:55,979 --> 00:20:57,645
[The Punisher grunting]

322
00:20:57,646 --> 00:20:58,978
[The Punisher groans]

323
00:20:58,979 --> 00:21:00,895
[bullets clanging]

324
00:21:00,896 --> 00:21:03,688
[groaning, screaming]

325
00:21:10,688 --> 00:21:12,478
- [screams]
- [rapid gunfire]

326
00:21:12,479 --> 00:21:14,771
[both grunting]

327
00:21:15,479 --> 00:21:17,354
[grunting]

328
00:21:19,521 --> 00:21:21,146
[grunting]

329
00:21:22,604 --> 00:21:25,020
- [grunts]
- [groans]

330
00:21:25,021 --> 00:21:28,103
- [knife clinks]
- [grunts]

331
00:21:28,104 --> 00:21:29,937
- [flesh squelching]
- [officer screaming]

332
00:21:29,938 --> 00:21:32,229
[♪ somber music playing]

333
00:21:35,813 --> 00:21:37,646
[grunting, panting]

334
00:21:39,729 --> 00:21:41,979
[officer grunting]

335
00:21:43,271 --> 00:21:45,188
[both grunting]

336
00:21:47,563 --> 00:21:48,563
[officer screams]

337
00:21:49,563 --> 00:21:51,728
- [cable whooshes, reels]
- [grunts]

338
00:21:51,729 --> 00:21:53,603
- [gunshot]
- [groans]

339
00:21:53,604 --> 00:21:56,396
[both panting]

340
00:22:00,729 --> 00:22:02,646
- [The Punisher] You good, Red?
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.

341
00:22:03,521 --> 00:22:04,604
[breathing heavily] Yeah, you?

342
00:22:04,896 --> 00:22:06,688
[The Punisher] Yeah.

343
00:22:08,396 --> 00:22:11,478
[both panting]

344
00:22:11,479 --> 00:22:13,938
- [Cole groans]
- [The Punisher] Hey, we found your guy.

345
00:22:15,271 --> 00:22:17,063
[bullet clinks]

346
00:22:18,563 --> 00:22:20,646
[♪ tense, suspenseful music playing]

347
00:22:24,063 --> 00:22:25,103
[Cole groans]

348
00:22:25,104 --> 00:22:27,437
[officer over radio] <i>Cole, come in.
Do you need backup?</i>

349
00:22:27,438 --> 00:22:29,271
Frank Castle's here. [groans]

350
00:22:30,396 --> 00:22:32,188
[continues groaning]

351
00:22:33,979 --> 00:22:35,521
[Daredevil] That yours? Huh?

352
00:22:36,563 --> 00:22:38,978
- Yeah. You recognize that?
- [Cole pants, groans]

353
00:22:38,979 --> 00:22:41,478
You killed Hector Ayala.

354
00:22:41,479 --> 00:22:43,104
[receiver chirps, clicks]

355
00:22:44,146 --> 00:22:45,271
He was a good man.

356
00:22:46,354 --> 00:22:47,979
[groans] Do what you gotta do.

357
00:22:48,896 --> 00:22:52,353
I stood with my own. I can die easy.

358
00:22:52,354 --> 00:22:54,521
[♪ somber music playing]

359
00:22:55,479 --> 00:22:57,563
[Daredevil breathing heavily]

360
00:22:58,521 --> 00:23:00,812
- [screams]
- [blood splatters]

361
00:23:00,813 --> 00:23:03,063
[Daredevil panting]

362
00:23:08,604 --> 00:23:10,437
[officer groans]

363
00:23:10,438 --> 00:23:12,271
[continues panting]

364
00:23:14,021 --> 00:23:16,021
[♪ somber music playing]

365
00:23:18,146 --> 00:23:20,271
[exhales] Yeah.

366
00:23:22,646 --> 00:23:24,103
[indistinct conversation]

367
00:23:24,104 --> 00:23:25,771
[imperceptible]

368
00:23:26,313 --> 00:23:27,353
[grunts]

369
00:23:27,354 --> 00:23:28,813
- Do it, Red.
- Yeah.

370
00:23:29,938 --> 00:23:33,770
- Come on, he's right there.
- You're not worth it. Not worth it.

371
00:23:33,771 --> 00:23:35,646
[both panting]

372
00:23:41,188 --> 00:23:44,853
No, Frank. No, no, no.
Please don't. It's not what I want.

373
00:23:44,854 --> 00:23:47,187
You get in front of a bullet
for this piece of shit too?

374
00:23:47,188 --> 00:23:49,645
- Is that what you do now, hero?
- He's not worth it, Frank.

375
00:23:49,646 --> 00:23:52,145
- [officer groaning]
- Not worth it. How about him?

376
00:23:52,146 --> 00:23:54,562
- He worth it? How about that? Huh?
- [groans]

377
00:23:54,563 --> 00:23:56,812
What is wrong with you?
You can't help yourself, can you?

378
00:23:56,813 --> 00:23:58,312
Goddamn hands off of me!

379
00:23:58,313 --> 00:24:00,312
You're a goddamn liability every time.

380
00:24:00,313 --> 00:24:02,895
- Good for you, blind boy.
- What is wrong with you? Shut up!

381
00:24:02,896 --> 00:24:04,187
[metallic clink]

382
00:24:04,188 --> 00:24:05,478
- Grenade.
- Huh?

383
00:24:05,479 --> 00:24:07,395
- [grenade clattering]
- [Daredevil] Run. Run, run!

384
00:24:07,396 --> 00:24:09,145
[♪ intense music playing]

385
00:24:09,146 --> 00:24:11,145
[The Punisher grunts]

386
00:24:11,146 --> 00:24:12,937
- [officer] Oh!
- [glass clattering]

387
00:24:12,938 --> 00:24:15,103
- [thud]
- [The Punisher grunts]

388
00:24:15,104 --> 00:24:17,353
- [explosion]
- [fire swooshing]

389
00:24:17,354 --> 00:24:19,063
[objects clattering]

390
00:24:20,021 --> 00:24:21,646
[sirens blaring]

391
00:24:25,146 --> 00:24:27,438
[both panting]

392
00:24:27,813 --> 00:24:29,437
[explosion]

393
00:24:29,438 --> 00:24:31,438
[objects clattering]

394
00:24:32,771 --> 00:24:35,437
[car alarms blaring]

395
00:24:35,438 --> 00:24:37,478
[Daredevil panting]

396
00:24:37,479 --> 00:24:38,938
[Daredevil] You're an asshole, Frank.

397
00:24:40,521 --> 00:24:41,521
[The Punisher] Yeah, I know.

398
00:24:42,646 --> 00:24:44,563
- [both pant]
- [engine revs]

399
00:24:46,354 --> 00:24:47,771
[tires screech]

400
00:24:50,646 --> 00:24:52,646
[♪ tense music playing]

401
00:25:03,646 --> 00:25:05,396
Come on, get in.

402
00:25:07,771 --> 00:25:09,063
- Shotgun.
- [chuckles]

403
00:25:10,563 --> 00:25:12,313
[The Punisher] Don't wanna hear your shit.

404
00:25:16,313 --> 00:25:18,353
[officer 1] <i>Copy, Three-Adam,
we need a couple more units</i>

405
00:25:18,354 --> 00:25:21,687
<i>- over here to help clear the area.</i>
- [Frank winces, groans]

406
00:25:21,688 --> 00:25:24,354
[officer 2] <i>Roger that, Charlie.
Three on point, assistance bare.</i>

407
00:25:25,729 --> 00:25:27,063
[officer 1] <i>Copy that. Confirmed.</i>

408
00:25:29,688 --> 00:25:30,853
How's it look?

409
00:25:30,854 --> 00:25:33,937
Well, you've been prettier. [sighs]

410
00:25:33,938 --> 00:25:35,188
[Matt chuckles]

411
00:25:39,271 --> 00:25:41,063
[Frank winces]

412
00:25:42,896 --> 00:25:45,604
What's going on? You called Frank, huh?

413
00:25:46,563 --> 00:25:49,396
[Karen] Uh-huh.
I heard Poindexter escaped.

414
00:25:50,438 --> 00:25:52,187
Called Frank and hopped on a plane.

415
00:25:52,188 --> 00:25:54,437
[♪ soft instrumental music playing]

416
00:25:54,438 --> 00:25:57,188
- [Frank groans softly]
- You couldn't call me?

417
00:25:59,521 --> 00:26:01,438
[Karen] I needed someone
to look out for you.

418
00:26:02,396 --> 00:26:04,396
You definitely wouldn't have liked that.

419
00:26:06,063 --> 00:26:07,771
[groans, sighs]

420
00:26:09,938 --> 00:26:11,979
- You okay over there?
- [Frank sighs]

421
00:26:12,688 --> 00:26:14,396
[Frank] Never been better. [sighs]

422
00:26:15,938 --> 00:26:18,063
[Karen] Come on. Let me take a look.

423
00:26:19,146 --> 00:26:20,728
- [pills rattling]
- Nah.

424
00:26:20,729 --> 00:26:23,353
- [♪ woman vocalizing]
- [crunching]

425
00:26:23,354 --> 00:26:25,146
[Frank] You know somethin', Karen?

426
00:26:26,146 --> 00:26:28,771
Nothin' in this world
a good cup of coffee can't fix.

427
00:26:31,938 --> 00:26:33,188
You want a cup?

428
00:26:36,271 --> 00:26:37,771
[clicks tongue] Uh, no, thank you.

429
00:26:45,354 --> 00:26:46,645
[sighs]

430
00:26:46,646 --> 00:26:49,104
[Frank] How about you, Red?
You want some coffee?

431
00:26:50,563 --> 00:26:52,728
- Got any oat milk?
- [Frank chuckles]

432
00:26:52,729 --> 00:26:55,228
- [objects clattering]
- [coffee trickling]

433
00:26:55,229 --> 00:27:00,063
So, he went after Matt Murdock,
not Daredevil. That's bold even for Fisk.

434
00:27:01,021 --> 00:27:03,188
Listen to me. Karen.
Turns out it was a hit...

435
00:27:04,438 --> 00:27:05,978
- on Foggy.
- [Karen] Holy shit.

436
00:27:05,979 --> 00:27:09,187
[Matt] Vanessa Fisk hired Poindexter
to take him out.

437
00:27:09,188 --> 00:27:10,353
- Why?
- [Matt breathes deeply]

438
00:27:10,354 --> 00:27:12,895
[Matt] I think there's something
in the motion he was about to file.

439
00:27:12,896 --> 00:27:14,978
He was moving to dismiss the case,

440
00:27:14,979 --> 00:27:17,062
and Vanessa made sure he never got to it.

441
00:27:17,063 --> 00:27:19,895
I think maybe
I missed something back then.

442
00:27:19,896 --> 00:27:22,313
You know, the files have been
in storage as far as I know.

443
00:27:22,938 --> 00:27:25,103
That's right. Will you be my eyes?

444
00:27:25,104 --> 00:27:26,813
- Hey, anytime.
- [Matt] Let's go.

445
00:27:32,896 --> 00:27:34,229
You comin', Frank?

446
00:27:35,604 --> 00:27:36,729
Got shit to do.

447
00:27:37,521 --> 00:27:39,812
[Matt] Realize Fisk will be coming
for you, too.

448
00:27:39,813 --> 00:27:40,895
[Frank] That right?

449
00:27:40,896 --> 00:27:44,646
I'll tell you what. If he does, I'll put
a bullet in his fat head. How about that?

450
00:27:45,479 --> 00:27:48,728
You know something? <i>Inspector Gadget</i>
bullshit... [sighs]

451
00:27:48,729 --> 00:27:49,895
...it's not for me.

452
00:27:49,896 --> 00:27:51,646
You guys can show yourselves out.

453
00:27:56,813 --> 00:27:58,479
[Karen] You know what, Frank?

454
00:28:00,521 --> 00:28:01,770
I'm not buyin' it.

455
00:28:01,771 --> 00:28:04,312
[♪ soft instrumental music playing]

456
00:28:04,313 --> 00:28:05,979
I don't believe you don't care.

457
00:28:12,188 --> 00:28:13,271
[Frank] Hey, Karen.

458
00:28:17,813 --> 00:28:20,813
You asked me for a favor. I did it.

459
00:28:24,229 --> 00:28:25,396
Yes, you did.

460
00:28:27,104 --> 00:28:28,229
Thank you.

461
00:28:35,896 --> 00:28:36,979
Stay safe.

462
00:28:38,771 --> 00:28:41,520
[woman] What the hell's going on?
It's the middle of the night.

463
00:28:41,521 --> 00:28:43,478
[Daniel] You've all had an opportunity
to look over

464
00:28:43,479 --> 00:28:45,728
Mayor Fisk's "Safer Street" initiative?

465
00:28:45,729 --> 00:28:47,228
Yes... [clears throat]

466
00:28:47,229 --> 00:28:49,020
- ...and it's insane.
- [Daniel] Oh.

467
00:28:49,021 --> 00:28:50,979
This makes
"Stop and Frisk" look like daycare.

468
00:28:51,729 --> 00:28:54,729
Deputy Speaker, "insane."

469
00:28:55,729 --> 00:28:56,937
What are you doin'?

470
00:28:56,938 --> 00:29:00,728
Mayor Fisk is super interested
in what the Council thinks.

471
00:29:00,729 --> 00:29:03,728
Especially those members
who aren't in enthusiastic support

472
00:29:03,729 --> 00:29:05,687
of his response to the city's crisis.

473
00:29:05,688 --> 00:29:07,228
That sounds like an enemies list.

474
00:29:07,229 --> 00:29:09,062
[Daniel] No, just outreach.

475
00:29:09,063 --> 00:29:12,728
Mayor Fisk cares deeply about
the City Council. Like you, Miss Speaker.

476
00:29:12,729 --> 00:29:16,270
He was so, so impressed with, um...
[clicks tongue]

477
00:29:16,271 --> 00:29:17,937
What was it again?

478
00:29:17,938 --> 00:29:20,937
[Buck] £540,000 stashed
in a Swiss Bank account.

479
00:29:20,938 --> 00:29:23,937
[Daniel] Right. Real estate investments
in Kips Bay, right?

480
00:29:23,938 --> 00:29:25,813
That, now, that's smart money.

481
00:29:26,396 --> 00:29:28,729
We should, you know, sit down
and share tips some time.

482
00:29:29,604 --> 00:29:32,437
Matter of fact,
Mayor Fisk is very interested

483
00:29:32,438 --> 00:29:34,396
in all the Council's accomplishments.

484
00:29:34,979 --> 00:29:36,103
We'd like to set meetings

485
00:29:36,104 --> 00:29:38,813
with each and every one of you
when the crisis has passed.

486
00:29:39,688 --> 00:29:41,854
Our office will reach out
to each of you shortly.

487
00:29:43,104 --> 00:29:44,146
Thank you, Buck.

488
00:29:45,854 --> 00:29:47,103
[sighs]

489
00:29:47,104 --> 00:29:49,895
The mayor will be addressin' the city
in a couple of hours.

490
00:29:49,896 --> 00:29:52,479
He hopes that Safer Streets
has your full support.

491
00:29:53,354 --> 00:29:55,103
If not, let us know.

492
00:29:55,104 --> 00:29:57,187
[♪ tense, suspenseful music playing]

493
00:29:57,188 --> 00:29:58,604
We'll make arrangements.

494
00:30:04,771 --> 00:30:07,687
{\an8}[indistinct screaming, shouting]

495
00:30:07,688 --> 00:30:09,562
{\an8}[BB] <i>How are you holding up out here?</i>

496
00:30:09,563 --> 00:30:13,853
{\an8}[man] <i>Yeah, so it's a blackout,
obviously, and there's--</i>

497
00:30:13,854 --> 00:30:15,728
{\an8}- [sirens blaring]
<i>- This one is that we have people</i>

498
00:30:15,729 --> 00:30:17,395
{\an8}<i>actually boarding up
their windows and doors</i>

499
00:30:17,396 --> 00:30:20,437
{\an8}<i>instead of metaphorically,
and then you have people who are looting,</i>

500
00:30:20,438 --> 00:30:25,271
{\an8}and then you have people like me who are
just kind of watching everything happen.

501
00:30:25,813 --> 00:30:27,478
{\an8}<i>Like, what else am I gonna do?</i>

502
00:30:27,479 --> 00:30:30,438
{\an8}[♪ intense music playing]

503
00:30:32,521 --> 00:30:36,062
- [officer] Freeze! Show me your hands!
- [objects clattering, thudding]

504
00:30:36,063 --> 00:30:38,062
- Hey.
- [metal rod rattling]

505
00:30:38,063 --> 00:30:39,354
[grunts]

506
00:30:40,021 --> 00:30:42,146
[people shouting indistinctly]

507
00:30:44,146 --> 00:30:45,979
Jesus, Burt, he's just a kid.

508
00:30:46,979 --> 00:30:49,438
No. It's not a kid.

509
00:30:52,479 --> 00:30:54,146
It's a masked vigilante.

510
00:30:57,563 --> 00:30:59,978
[Matt] I can't believe I didn't check
what he didn't fill out.

511
00:30:59,979 --> 00:31:01,645
[Karen] Matt, don't beat
yourself up, okay?

512
00:31:01,646 --> 00:31:02,813
We were all hurting.

513
00:31:06,188 --> 00:31:07,521
[Matt] So... [clears throat]

514
00:31:08,979 --> 00:31:10,313
you talk to Frank a lot?

515
00:31:11,771 --> 00:31:12,896
[chuckles]

516
00:31:13,938 --> 00:31:14,938
What?

517
00:31:15,729 --> 00:31:17,229
You sound like you're jealous.

518
00:31:19,354 --> 00:31:21,896
You know, back at his place,
I heard your heartbeats.

519
00:31:22,646 --> 00:31:24,438
God, that is really not fair.

520
00:31:28,521 --> 00:31:29,563
You heard his too?

521
00:31:30,729 --> 00:31:31,729
Oh, yeah.

522
00:31:33,479 --> 00:31:35,228
It's just adrenaline, I'm sure.

523
00:31:35,229 --> 00:31:37,271
[♪ soft, melancholy music playing]

524
00:31:38,438 --> 00:31:40,104
You hear mine when I saw you?

525
00:31:43,354 --> 00:31:44,563
Yeah.

526
00:31:45,563 --> 00:31:46,563
Yeah?

527
00:31:49,604 --> 00:31:50,938
Adrenaline, I'm sure.

528
00:31:58,771 --> 00:31:59,771
Oh, wow.

529
00:32:00,604 --> 00:32:02,021
[object rustling]

530
00:32:02,938 --> 00:32:04,063
I packed this one.

531
00:32:05,813 --> 00:32:09,853
Oh, man. "Avocados at Law."

532
00:32:09,854 --> 00:32:11,562
You know, I never got that joke.

533
00:32:11,563 --> 00:32:13,145
<i>- Abogados.</i>
- [Karen] <i>Abogados!</i>

534
00:32:13,146 --> 00:32:14,687
[both] Spanish for "lawyers."

535
00:32:14,688 --> 00:32:16,145
- [Matt] Right?
- Of course.

536
00:32:16,146 --> 00:32:18,812
Foggy was really drunk one night and...
[breathes deeply]

537
00:32:18,813 --> 00:32:19,895
I don't know, it was stupid,

538
00:32:19,896 --> 00:32:22,854
- it somehow became "Avocados at Law."
- [chuckles]

539
00:32:24,313 --> 00:32:26,478
- [object clatters]
- [Matt] Hmm.

540
00:32:26,479 --> 00:32:28,729
[♪ soft instrumental music playing]

541
00:32:37,438 --> 00:32:38,604
I'm glad you're back.

542
00:32:43,271 --> 00:32:44,521
[sighs]

543
00:32:51,021 --> 00:32:52,687
[Karen] Hey, this is it.

544
00:32:52,688 --> 00:32:54,521
- [straining] A year and a half ago.
- [box thuds]

545
00:32:57,479 --> 00:33:00,020
Yes! Okay, here's the motion Foggy filed.

546
00:33:00,021 --> 00:33:01,603
- Right.
- Good work, Karen Page.

547
00:33:01,604 --> 00:33:02,688
Well...

548
00:33:04,646 --> 00:33:08,395
Foggy was gonna argue that... Whoa.

549
00:33:08,396 --> 00:33:10,603
"Due to the unique nature
of the Red Hook Port location,

550
00:33:10,604 --> 00:33:14,353
"no crime was committed in New York state
or even the United States of America.

551
00:33:14,354 --> 00:33:16,687
"Therefore, the court has no jurisdiction
to prosecute."

552
00:33:16,688 --> 00:33:18,979
- What?
- Wait, there's a photocopy.

553
00:33:19,854 --> 00:33:20,895
Aah.

554
00:33:20,896 --> 00:33:24,146
"Red Hook Charter, 1855."

555
00:33:25,146 --> 00:33:27,063
Holy crap, it's a free port.

556
00:33:28,521 --> 00:33:32,437
Exempt from the jurisdiction of the city,
and the country, for that matter.

557
00:33:32,438 --> 00:33:34,396
What would that have to do with the Fisks?

558
00:33:35,104 --> 00:33:39,270
[exhales] Well, Vanessa has used the port
to store art for years now.

559
00:33:39,271 --> 00:33:42,145
I mean, if it's a free port, she's doing
it without customs, without taxation,

560
00:33:42,146 --> 00:33:43,520
without fear of seizures.

561
00:33:43,521 --> 00:33:45,478
- She could launder money legally.
- Right.

562
00:33:45,479 --> 00:33:48,645
And now, our mayor is building
a new complex there.

563
00:33:48,646 --> 00:33:50,395
This charter would make it untouchable.

564
00:33:50,396 --> 00:33:53,187
Gambling, smuggling,
you name it, all of it legal.

565
00:33:53,188 --> 00:33:57,271
God, Foggy had no idea what he stumbled
into. He thought it was a truck robbery.

566
00:33:58,479 --> 00:34:02,313
No, this is about the Fisks
building their own city state.

567
00:34:03,396 --> 00:34:05,103
Let's go see what they're hiding.

568
00:34:05,104 --> 00:34:07,104
[shutter rattling]

569
00:34:08,146 --> 00:34:10,146
[♪ dramatic music playing]

570
00:34:10,979 --> 00:34:12,313
[people screaming]

571
00:34:13,896 --> 00:34:15,228
- [explosion]
- [glass breaking]

572
00:34:15,229 --> 00:34:17,270
[officer 1] <i>What's the status report?</i>

573
00:34:17,271 --> 00:34:19,187
[officer 2] <i>No eyes on Murdock
and the blonde.</i>

574
00:34:19,188 --> 00:34:20,853
<i>Daredevil and Punisher got away.</i>

575
00:34:20,854 --> 00:34:25,228
[officer 1] <i>Jesus. Fall back to Red Hook.
Let's go huntin'.</i>

576
00:34:25,229 --> 00:34:26,812
- [sighs]
- [radio beeps]

577
00:34:26,813 --> 00:34:29,646
<i>Copy that. Falling back
to rendezvous one, Red Hook.</i>

578
00:34:30,771 --> 00:34:32,771
[♪ dramatic music playing]

579
00:34:38,104 --> 00:34:40,229
[engine revving]

580
00:34:47,854 --> 00:34:49,813
- [grunts]
- [muffled groaning]

581
00:34:50,688 --> 00:34:52,270
[blood squelching]

582
00:34:52,271 --> 00:34:54,354
[♪ eerie music playing]

583
00:35:07,646 --> 00:35:09,895
- [officer 1] What if he's actually here?
- [officer 2] Oh, shit!

584
00:35:09,896 --> 00:35:11,479
- It's Punisher!
- [officer 3] It's Castle.

585
00:35:14,813 --> 00:35:16,228
[♪ eerie music playing]

586
00:35:16,229 --> 00:35:17,813
[The Punisher grunting]

587
00:35:19,938 --> 00:35:21,937
- [officer 1] Non-lethals only.
- [officer 2] Don't shoot!

588
00:35:21,938 --> 00:35:23,520
[officer 1] Frank, stay calm.

589
00:35:23,521 --> 00:35:25,145
- We just wanna talk.
- [The Punisher grunts]

590
00:35:25,146 --> 00:35:26,770
[all grunting]

591
00:35:26,771 --> 00:35:27,979
[grunting]

592
00:35:32,146 --> 00:35:33,478
[all grunting]

593
00:35:33,479 --> 00:35:34,937
- [gunshot]
- [weapon clangs]

594
00:35:34,938 --> 00:35:36,145
[officer groans]

595
00:35:36,146 --> 00:35:37,813
- [grunts]
- [thuds]

596
00:35:40,813 --> 00:35:43,603
[all grunting]

597
00:35:43,604 --> 00:35:44,687
[metal clangs]

598
00:35:44,688 --> 00:35:46,395
[officer, straining] No, no! No, no, no!

599
00:35:46,396 --> 00:35:48,021
- [grunting]
- [blood splatters]

600
00:35:56,104 --> 00:36:00,603
- [gunshot]
- [grunting]

601
00:36:00,604 --> 00:36:03,437
- [gunshot]
- [indistinct shouting]

602
00:36:03,438 --> 00:36:04,813
[officer 1] Get him!

603
00:36:05,354 --> 00:36:07,187
- [officer 2] Get him!
- [screaming indistinctly]

604
00:36:07,188 --> 00:36:08,520
[officer 3] Get him up!

605
00:36:08,521 --> 00:36:09,728
[indistinct shouting]

606
00:36:09,729 --> 00:36:11,645
- [grunts]
- [blood splatters]

607
00:36:11,646 --> 00:36:13,188
[officer 1] Get him!

608
00:36:13,771 --> 00:36:14,854
[The Punisher grunts]

609
00:36:16,021 --> 00:36:17,521
[screaming indistinctly]

610
00:36:20,854 --> 00:36:24,270
[Gallo] <i>I'm going up the ladder.
Governor, State Supreme Court.</i>

611
00:36:24,271 --> 00:36:27,353
<i>Look, this is still the mayor's office.
It's not the Kingpin's.</i>

612
00:36:27,354 --> 00:36:29,563
<i>And he is still subject to the law.</i>

613
00:36:30,479 --> 00:36:34,563
<i>And I'm hoping for your support.</i>

614
00:36:36,438 --> 00:36:37,562
[Sheila] <i>When?</i>

615
00:36:37,563 --> 00:36:40,438
[Gallo] <i>Tomorrow. I'm leavin' for Albany
first thing.</i>

616
00:36:42,021 --> 00:36:44,438
[Sheila] <i>Well, there's no way
I can go with you.</i>

617
00:36:45,979 --> 00:36:48,937
- [sniffles]
<i>- But if you need me to put in a word,</i>

618
00:36:48,938 --> 00:36:50,104
<i>you got it.</i>

619
00:36:51,063 --> 00:36:52,438
[Gallo] <i>I appreciate that, Sheila.</i>

620
00:36:54,021 --> 00:36:56,021
[♪ tense music playing]

621
00:36:58,688 --> 00:37:00,478
[breathes deeply, exhales]

622
00:37:00,479 --> 00:37:03,187
Just take me home, Mario.
[breath trembles]

623
00:37:03,188 --> 00:37:04,937
[door opens]

624
00:37:04,938 --> 00:37:06,603
[man] Mario got sick.

625
00:37:06,604 --> 00:37:08,604
[♪ tense music continues playing]

626
00:37:09,646 --> 00:37:10,854
[Gallo] Wait, Luke?

627
00:37:11,688 --> 00:37:13,562
[chuckles] Haven't seen you
in a long time,

628
00:37:13,563 --> 00:37:15,021
not since you were a rookie, huh?

629
00:37:15,896 --> 00:37:19,146
- [Luke] Yeah... long time ago.
- [siren blaring]

630
00:37:20,771 --> 00:37:22,188
It's fresh ink, huh?

631
00:37:23,271 --> 00:37:24,771
You're part of the Task Force?

632
00:37:25,896 --> 00:37:27,396
The mayor recruited me.

633
00:37:28,938 --> 00:37:30,979
- [car engine starts]
- [chuckles softly]

634
00:37:32,021 --> 00:37:33,188
[Luke] Just tryna survive.

635
00:37:33,854 --> 00:37:35,396
- [door opens]
- Yeah, I know.

636
00:37:36,854 --> 00:37:38,354
[sighs]

637
00:37:39,229 --> 00:37:41,145
[♪ dramatic music playing]

638
00:37:41,146 --> 00:37:43,188
[people talking indistinctly]

639
00:37:55,729 --> 00:37:57,688
[♪ dramatic music playing]

640
00:37:58,938 --> 00:38:01,646
- [metal rattling]
- [sighs]

641
00:38:02,729 --> 00:38:04,646
[♪ eerie music playing]

642
00:38:06,021 --> 00:38:07,396
[Powell exhales]

643
00:38:09,479 --> 00:38:11,729
It's an honor to meet you, Castle.
[chuckles softly]

644
00:38:12,729 --> 00:38:14,396
I'm a big admirer of your work.

645
00:38:15,979 --> 00:38:17,396
Jesus Christ.

646
00:38:18,396 --> 00:38:20,563
[Powell] And I lost a lot of guys
'cause of you today.

647
00:38:23,229 --> 00:38:25,188
And I'm hopin'
that this is fuckin' worth it.

648
00:38:29,229 --> 00:38:31,313
Listen, Frank, everything that you do,

649
00:38:32,521 --> 00:38:36,979
you know, you can do that with us,
and you don't gotta run anymore.

650
00:38:38,563 --> 00:38:42,021
These guys fuckin' idolize you, man.
We all do.

651
00:38:44,979 --> 00:38:47,103
It'd be an honor to serve with you, Frank.

652
00:38:47,104 --> 00:38:49,021
[♪ tense dramatic music playing]

653
00:38:53,354 --> 00:38:55,353
[Gallo] <i>You know,
you'll never get away with this.</i>

654
00:38:55,354 --> 00:38:57,146
I'm still the goddamn Commissioner.

655
00:38:58,396 --> 00:39:00,437
[Buck] New York is standing
with Mayor Fisk.

656
00:39:00,438 --> 00:39:01,812
[Fisk talking indistinctly]

657
00:39:01,813 --> 00:39:05,354
It's made its choice.
We're just honoring it.

658
00:39:07,021 --> 00:39:08,603
Oh, you're outta your goddamn mind.

659
00:39:08,604 --> 00:39:09,938
[Fisk] You understand?

660
00:39:10,896 --> 00:39:14,229
[Gallo] There are easier ways to see me,
Mayor Fisk.

661
00:39:15,313 --> 00:39:16,438
Not me.

662
00:39:18,771 --> 00:39:20,020
They see you...

663
00:39:20,021 --> 00:39:23,187
But you were never really there
for the rank and file, were you?

664
00:39:23,188 --> 00:39:25,103
You know, the men and women
on the front line

665
00:39:25,104 --> 00:39:29,063
risking their lives
to keep New York safe...

666
00:39:30,063 --> 00:39:31,688
keep you safe.

667
00:39:32,479 --> 00:39:35,979
I wonder, can we blame the Commissioner?

668
00:39:36,479 --> 00:39:40,771
I mean, after all,
he's just a cog in a broken machine.

669
00:39:43,813 --> 00:39:45,896
[♪ tense music playing]

670
00:39:50,146 --> 00:39:52,103
- You admire me, huh?
- [Powell] Yeah.

671
00:39:52,104 --> 00:39:54,229
Yeah. Hey...

672
00:39:55,688 --> 00:39:57,688
Out of your fuckin' mind, you know that?

673
00:39:59,604 --> 00:40:01,604
You're a bunch of clowns, you know that?

674
00:40:03,938 --> 00:40:05,354
You fuckin' clowns.

675
00:40:06,729 --> 00:40:07,979
Admire me.

676
00:40:10,021 --> 00:40:11,604
You think you know my pain?

677
00:40:14,104 --> 00:40:15,853
You think you know my loss?

678
00:40:15,854 --> 00:40:18,229
[♪ tense music continues playing]

679
00:40:20,021 --> 00:40:21,188
Yeah, I was right.

680
00:40:23,438 --> 00:40:27,521
You... never stopped being Kingpin.

681
00:40:29,479 --> 00:40:30,521
You can't.

682
00:40:33,229 --> 00:40:34,770
[The Punisher] <i>You admire me?</i>

683
00:40:34,771 --> 00:40:36,313
What do you know about me?

684
00:40:37,104 --> 00:40:40,771
How I see the world?
You know how I see the world?

685
00:40:43,854 --> 00:40:46,063
[groans, chokes]

686
00:40:47,438 --> 00:40:48,813
[groans]

687
00:40:50,396 --> 00:40:53,354
It's just a circus. A bunch of clowns.

688
00:40:54,604 --> 00:40:56,312
I ain't gonna serve with you.

689
00:40:56,313 --> 00:40:59,478
I won't fuckin' piss on you
if you were on fire, you got that?

690
00:40:59,479 --> 00:41:00,895
I'm sorry to hear that, Frank.

691
00:41:00,896 --> 00:41:02,521
- [The Punisher] Are you?
- Yeah.

692
00:41:04,354 --> 00:41:05,354
[The Punisher] What's that?

693
00:41:06,271 --> 00:41:08,104
What about you? You sorry?

694
00:41:08,688 --> 00:41:10,021
[groaning]

695
00:41:12,438 --> 00:41:13,604
Not so bad.

696
00:41:15,021 --> 00:41:16,645
- [groaning]
- [bones cracking]

697
00:41:16,646 --> 00:41:18,063
[Fisk] We...

698
00:41:19,438 --> 00:41:23,603
- We will keep this city safe.
- [bones cracking]

699
00:41:23,604 --> 00:41:25,312
- [Gallo groans]
- [The Punisher shouts]

700
00:41:25,313 --> 00:41:26,979
- [punch thuds loudly]
- [The Punisher groans]

701
00:41:30,688 --> 00:41:33,146
I'm still here. [panting]

702
00:41:34,813 --> 00:41:36,313
- [officer grunts]
- [groans]

703
00:41:37,563 --> 00:41:40,478
- [bones cracking]
- [Fisk] <i>We will not let anyone...</i>

704
00:41:40,479 --> 00:41:42,271
[groaning]

705
00:41:43,479 --> 00:41:46,104
- ...threaten our homes.
- [screaming]

706
00:41:48,646 --> 00:41:50,063
- [grunts]
- [blood splashing]

707
00:41:51,354 --> 00:41:53,021
- [officers groan]
- [blood spluttering]

708
00:41:54,563 --> 00:41:56,021
[jaw clattering]

709
00:41:58,896 --> 00:42:00,188
[exhales]

710
00:42:05,021 --> 00:42:06,313
[sighs]

711
00:42:07,438 --> 00:42:08,979
Any questions?

712
00:42:12,938 --> 00:42:15,645
Good. Good.

713
00:42:15,646 --> 00:42:17,729
[unsettling music playing]

714
00:42:21,188 --> 00:42:22,729
[sirens blaring]

715
00:42:25,271 --> 00:42:26,896
[people talking indistinctly]

716
00:42:31,646 --> 00:42:35,312
[sighs] Shit.
It's crawling with Task Force.

717
00:42:35,313 --> 00:42:36,771
[grunts, breathes heavily]

718
00:42:41,021 --> 00:42:43,728
- [officer] Hey, 40! Spread out! Let's go!
- [indistinct radio chatter]

719
00:42:43,729 --> 00:42:45,270
[groans]

720
00:42:45,271 --> 00:42:47,353
All right, I'm goin' in, stay here,
stay out of sight.

721
00:42:47,354 --> 00:42:51,353
No! Look, it'll be Josie's all over again.

722
00:42:51,354 --> 00:42:53,354
You go in there, you will die...

723
00:42:54,396 --> 00:42:56,146
- or you will kill.
- [Matt groans]

724
00:42:56,771 --> 00:42:58,146
Now you're hurt.

725
00:42:58,896 --> 00:43:02,770
You will not survive.
Is that what you want?

726
00:43:02,771 --> 00:43:05,021
[breathing heavily]

727
00:43:07,479 --> 00:43:08,813
Look, Fisk has the courts...

728
00:43:09,396 --> 00:43:11,478
He's got the cops, he's got an army.

729
00:43:11,479 --> 00:43:15,228
Now, you can go down there, and you can
fight him, and you will probably die,

730
00:43:15,229 --> 00:43:18,853
but you can't beat him. Not like that.
You have to be smart.

731
00:43:18,854 --> 00:43:20,813
[people screaming distantly]

732
00:43:21,729 --> 00:43:23,103
I'm right there with you, okay?

733
00:43:23,104 --> 00:43:25,728
I feel lost, I feel angry,
I feel fucking helpless.

734
00:43:25,729 --> 00:43:27,313
The whole city is there.

